<BaseLayout
  title="Medical Disclaimer"
  description="TheWellnessGPT is educational and is not a substitute for professional medical advice. See a doctor or pharmacist for diagnosis, prescription treatment, or severe acne."
  lang="en"
  market="sg"
>
  <article class="article">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h1>Medical disclaimer</h1>
      <div class="article-body">
        <p>TheWellnessGPT publishes educational information about skincare, built for skin in Singapore, the climate here, and what you can buy locally. It is written carefully and sourced responsibly, but it is general information, not personal medical advice.</p>

        <h2>This is not a substitute for a professional</h2>
        <p>Nothing on this site is a diagnosis or a treatment plan for your specific situation. Skin is individual. If you are unsure what you are dealing with, a doctor or pharmacist can assess you properly in minutes.</p>

        <h2>When to see a doctor</h2>
        <p>Please seek professional care if your acne is severe, painful, cystic or nodular; if it is leaving scars; if it has not improved after a few months of consistent over-the-counter care; or if it is affecting your confidence or mental health.</p>

        <h2>Prescription treatments</h2>
        <p>Some treatments we describe (for example stronger retinoids, or oral medication) are prescription or pharmacist-guided in Singapore. Use them only under appropriate guidance, and follow the product label. If you are pregnant, breastfeeding, or taking other medication, check with a professional before starting any active treatment.</p>

        <h2>Individual results vary</h2>
        <p>Ingredients and products affect people differently. Patch-test new products, introduce one active at a time, and stop using anything that causes persistent irritation. If a reaction is severe, seek medical help.</p>

        <p>By using this site you understand that TheWellnessGPT and its editors are not responsible for decisions made based on this general information. When in doubt, talk to a professional.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
